Creating a simple button click function to get familiar withÂ HTML:
The code below modifies text when a button is clicked.

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Button Click Example</title>
    <script>
        function changeText() {
            document.getElementbyId("text")>innerHTML = "You clicked the button!";
        }
    </script>
</head>
<body>
  <h2 id="text">Click the button below</h2>
  <button onClick="changeText()">Click Me</button>
</body>
</html>

Creating a Random number generator:
the function below is another HTML script that is used to generate and display a random number when a button is clicked.

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Random Number Generator</title>
    <script>
        function generateNumber() {
            let randomNum = Math.floor(Math.random() * 100) + 1;
            document.getElementById("result").innerHTML = "Random Number: " + randomNum;
        }
    </script>
</head>
<body>
    <h2 id="result">Click the button to get a random number</h2>
    <button onclick="generateNumber()">Generate</button>
</body>
</html>
